<item>
            <title>[SOLR-4055] Remove/Reload the collection has the thread safe issue.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4055</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;OverseerCollectionProcessor class for collectionCmd method has thread safe issue.&lt;br/&gt;
The major issue is ModifiableSolrParams params instance will deliver into other thread use(HttpShardHandler.submit). Modify parameter will affect the other threads the correct parameter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the method collectionCmd , change the value params.set(CoreAdminParams.CORE, node.getStr(ZkStateReader.CORE_NAME_PROP)); , that occur send the http request thread will get the wrong core name. The result is that can&apos;t delete/reload the right core.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The easy fix is clone the ModifiableSolrParams for every request.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Solr cloud&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
